# Global Rules

## Primary Principles
- Never write hardcoded screen resolutions or display swap flags — always read configurations from `useDeviceStore` dynamically.
- All colors exported to C must go through the converter in `src/utils/lvglColor.js`.
- All coordinates exported to C must go through `src/utils/lvglCoord.js`.
- Do not modify template handlebars files under `src/engine/templates/` without explicit authorization.
- Do not install new dependencies in `package.json` without user approval.

## Code Style
- Use React functional components with custom hooks.
- Use named exports for all layout files, utilities, and components (except React Router Pages which default-export page structures).
- Global state must be managed with Zustand. Component-level states use useState/useReducer.
- Avoid prop drilling past 2 levels; leverage Zustand stores when sharing widget metadata.

## Naming Conventions
- React components: PascalCase (e.g. `ClockWidget.jsx`).
- Utility hooks and scripts: camelCase (e.g. `useWidgetDrag.js`).
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE.
- Zustand store actions: `verbNoun` pattern (e.g. `addWidget`, `removeScreen`).
